song_name: The Thing That Should Not Be

version_description: Hey guys. Found out that the chords you find in the web are a little bit difficult for beginners to play along with. I placed the chords at the "right" position above the lyrics. The ending and the chords beneath the solo are easier to play while listening the song.
I had always some difficulties with the existing scripts and they wasn't precise enough. Therefore I heard it out for myself. Now I make it available.

All of the publications about this song in the UG Site corresponds to the Thin Lizzy version of it. This are the chords used by Metallica for this version on the 1998's Garage Inc Album, and do NOT correspond to the chords used by Thin Lizzy on the original record. Thank you for your time.

Well-aligned chords for all parts of the song / tab for coda lick / intermediate version with slash chords / suggestions for playable voicings / second version for Drop-D tuning with tab part and playing suggestions.
An easy standard tuning chord version, mostly based around a sliding E chord shape with open strings, chord legend included.
Complete chords and lyrics / capo 2nd fret to match original recording /.
